⭐ MVC Framework (Complete Viva Answer)
🔷 What is MVC?

MVC (Model–View–Controller) is a software architectural pattern used to design applications by separating them into three interconnected components:

Model
View
Controller

It helps in organizing code, separating logic, and improving maintainability.

🔷 1. Model
Represents data and business logic
Works with database
Stores and manages application data
Example:
User details (name, age)
Product information
Database records
🔷 2. View
Represents user interface (UI)
What user sees on screen
Displays data from Model
Example:
Web page (HTML)
Forms
Tables, buttons
🔷 3. Controller
Acts as a middle layer
Takes input from user
Sends commands to Model
Returns output to View
Example:
Login button click handling
Form submission processing
🔷 MVC Flow (Very Important for Viva)
User → Controller → Model → Controller → View → User

Explanation:
User sends request
Controller receives request
Controller updates/gets data from Model
Model processes data
Controller sends data to View
View displays result to user
🔷 Real-Life Example (Easy to remember)

👉 Online shopping app:

Model: Product data, cart data, user data
View: Website pages (cart page, product page)
Controller: Add to cart, checkout process
🔷 Advantages of MVC
✔ Separation of concerns (easy debugging)
✔ Code reusability
✔ Easy maintenance
✔ Parallel development (UI + backend separately)
✔ Scalable applications
🔷 Where MVC is used?
Web frameworks:
ASP.NET MVC
Django
Spring MVC
Laravel
🔷 Viva Short Definition (Important)

👉 “MVC is a design pattern that divides an application into Model (data), View (UI), and Controller (logic) to separate concerns and improve code organization.”
